  "market_context": "NQ 1-minute chart on 7/12/2023 showing an ascending sequence into roughly 16180, followed by a sharp rejection lower. The analyst rewinds the price action to compare two entry methods after price tops out and begins to break down toward a prior low near 16150.",
  "key_observation": "Once price closed below the series of up-close candles (change in state of delivery), an earlier short was available via the order block retest, the fair value gap inside it, or the 0.5 mean threshold. The later market structure shift never offered a retracement entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the swing high and note price closing below the series of up-close candles, validating that group as a bearish order block and signalling a change in state of delivery to bearish.",
    "Mark the old low as the downside draw on liquidity and wait to see if structure shifts.",
    "Observe that displacement and a close below the swing low eventually occur (market structure shift), but price runs the old low without any retracement, offering no MSS entry.",
    "Rewind and demonstrate CISD-based entries: a short at the order block retest with stop above the high, an entry at the fair value gap inside the order block, and an entry at the 0.5 mean threshold of the order block.",
    "Show price tagging the mean threshold and then reaching the target (RTP) at the old low.",
    "Contrast with a second example where CISD triggered but no displacement/MSS occurred — warning that CISD entries can be earlier but also lead to losers when structure never confirms."
  ],
  "outcome": "CISD-based short entries (order block retest, FVG, mean threshold) reached the target at the prior low; the MSS approach offered no entry because price never retraced.",
  "lessons": "Change in state of delivery can provide earlier entries than a market structure shift, with the order block, internal fair value gap, and 0.5 mean threshold all serving as valid entry points — but CISD without a subsequent MSS can fail, so the trade-off must be respected.",
